CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1956, pg. A27 reads: "Leaving Altar - After their valentine evening wedding, Mr. and Mrs. Edmon Davis are shown leaving the altar at Faith Evangelical Church on Ewart Drive. The bride is the former Dorothy Jackson, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Horace Jackson, 6628 Deary Street.  The Rev. and Mrs. E.D. Davis, 3722 Frazier Street, are parents of the groom - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Edmon Davis and bride Dorothy Jackson Davis, posed in front of altar in Faith Evangelical Church, Ewart Drive
